<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>like a dream • like in a dream</xh5><p> <i>like a dream—</i>1. like smth. imaginary or unreal: How could a cat appear in my apartment? I looked up, and for a moment I thought the cat had vanished <u>like a dream</u>. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> said of smth. that functions exceptionally well: The car goes <u>like a dream</u> but I should get the belts changed just in case.</p><p> <i>like in a dream</i>—(also: as in a dream) 1. perceived like some illusory images seen in a dream: My recollection of that event is hazy.... It was so unreal. <u>Like in a dream</u>. 2. said of smb. living out of contact with reality: I have been living <u>like in a dream</u> until your tenderness and love warmed me.</p> </entry>
